Policy_Details: - Sell or distribute tickets in advance of the event;
- Have a maximum of 50 persons, including attendees, performers, staff, and all other persons in the venue;
- Reserve seating with individuals or groups (of no more than 6 persons) seated at least 6 feet apart
- Place seats at least 30 ft. from the stage if there is live singing; otherwise, the seats must be placed at least 20 ft. from the stage
- Require that guests remain seated during the performance, only leaving as necessary
- Ensure good ventilation;
- Clean the venue and restrooms in accordance with your plan;
- Maintain a one-way flow of attendees and staff
- If the performance is indoors it must be less than 3 hours in duration;
- Require the performers to be at least 6  feet apart and wear masks when not performing;
- Inform your employees of the COVID-19 protocols you have put in place, including a mask or face covering policy and any applicable leave policies
- Maintain records of all individuals who are in the building during the event
- Post signage of your mask or face covering guidelines and physical guides or signs of your social distancing policies
- Inform any individual who is exhibiting symptoms of COVID-19 to not attend the event.   Source information: https://coronavirus.dc.gov/phasetwo
